        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-08-13 14:00:43.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nKeong, thats not necessary the case, its whose changes get merged first, the other person will have to rebase and integrate their changes.\nFor your second question, the yaml and html documentation will be found in maven like this:\nhttps://nexus.onap.org/service/local/repositories/releases/archive/org/onap/aai/aai-common/aai-schema/1.2.4/aai-schema-1.2.4.jar/!/aai_swagger_html/aai_swagger_v13.html\n\nThe main reason to do this is because we can't push an html file. It looks like gerrit limited the size of a file so I won't be able to push my v14 yaml and html files due to that.\n\nWhen you run mvn clean install -DskipTests it will generate it in your local repo so you can see them there.",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
